description:
The web development team needs a lightweight JSON feed for the 'Recent Earthquakes' widget as they cannot parse complex SeisComP XML. Write a Python script at ~/Documents/export_latest_json.py that connects to the SeisComP database (mysql://sysop:sysop@localhost/seiscomp) to retrieve the most recent earthquake event, including its origin and magnitude details. Export the results to ~/Documents/latest_event.json using the following schema:

{
  "public_id": "string (e.g. the event publicID)",
  "description": "string (the event description text)",
  "timestamp": "string (ISO 8601 format)",
  "location": {
    "latitude": float,
    "longitude": float,
    "depth_km": float
  },
  "magnitude": {
    "value": float,
    "type": "string"
  }
}
